explanation: This solution uses a stack to keep track of the opening brackets and a hash map to map closing brackets to their corresponding opening brackets. It iterates through the string, pushing opening brackets onto the stack and popping them off when a matching closing bracket is encountered. If a closing bracket does not match the top of the stack or if there are unmatched opening brackets left at the end, the string is invalid. This approach has a high efficiency due to its constant time complexity for stack operations and hash map lookups.

